articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Hong Kong-listed shares of China's Alibaba Group (9988.HK) fell more than 4% on Monday after the surprise departure of outgoing Alibaba CEO Daniel Zhang from the company's cloud computing business.
articles.title: Alibaba shares slide 4% after outgoing CEO quits cloud unit

articles.author: Yu Xie
articles.description: Embattled developer Country Garden faces a new round of voting by creditors to extend several debt maturities on Monday, after having avoided default at the last minute twice this month to bring some respite to the crisis-hit Chinese property sector.
articles.title: Country Garden faces fresh test for onshore bond extensions

articles.author: Echo Wang, Anirban Sen
articles.description: Arm, the chip designer owned by SoftBank Group Corp (9984.T), is getting close to securing enough investor support to attain the fully diluted valuation of $54.5 billion it was seeking in its initial public offering (IPO) at the top of its indicated range, and is considering asking investors to value it higher, people familiar with the matter said on Sunday.
articles.title: Exclusive: SoftBank's Arm eyes pricing IPO at top of range or above

articles.author: Kevin Yao, Joe Cash
articles.description: China's consumer prices returned to positive territory in August while factory-gate price declines slowed, data showed on Saturday, as deflation pressures ease amid signs of stabilisation in the economy.
articles.title: China's deflation pressures ease, more steps expected to spur demand

articles.author: Lewis Jackson, Roushni Nair
articles.description: Chevron Australia (CVX.N) no longer expects to reach a deal with unions and will instead pursue an untested legal strategy to stop industrial action at its Gorgon and Wheatstone liquefied natural gas days before it escalates into full strikes.
articles.title: Chevron gambles on untested laws to halt Australia LNG strike action

articles.author: Valerie Volcovici
articles.description: The prime ministers of two small island nations that face ongoing impacts from rising sea levels will appear at legal hearings at an international court in Hamburg, Germany, on Monday, and seek an advisory opinion on the obligations of countries to combat climate change.
articles.title: Island states seek climate protection from Law of the Sea

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Grocery delivery service Instacart is targeting a valuation between $8.6 billion and $9.3 billion in its initial public offering, according to a person familiar with the matter.
articles.title: Instacart to target valuation of up to $9.3 billion in IPO, source says

articles.author: Jihed Abidellaoui, Alexander Cornwell
articles.description: Rescuers searched on Sunday for survivors of Morocco's deadliest earthquake in more than six decades, with more than 2,000 people killed by the disaster that has laid waste to villages in the mountains outside Marrakech.
articles.title: Rescuers hunt for survivors of Morocco quake with over 2,000 dead

articles.author: Nandita Bose, Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden said on Sunday he held his highest-level talks with Chinese leadership in months, adding that Beijing's economic wobbles would not lead it to invade Taiwan.
articles.title: Biden meets China leader Li, says economic woes make Taiwan invasion less likely

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia on Sunday wrapped up widely denounced regional and municipal elections, including in regions annexed from Ukraine, delivering strong support for President Vladimir Putin amidst criticism of vote rigging and Kyiv's push to reclaim its land.
articles.title: Russian regional vote delivers strong result for Putin amid claims of rigging
